<TITLE> Kofi Annan delays Kenya mission due to severe flu </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 GENEVA, Jan 15 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Former United Nations Secretary-General Kofi Annan has severe flu and will not immediately travel to Kenya, where he was due to help mediate a political crisis, his office said on Tuesday. "On advice of doctors he has postponed his mission to Nairobi for a few days," Annan's office said in a statement released in Geneva.
